Collectively, the controls and processes defined in sections A.10 through A.18 establish a significantly stronger provider supply-chain model than unmanaged, manual, or developer-driven approaches. This model ensures that all Terraform providers are introduced through a controlled, auditable pipeline with explicit GIS and Security approval, clear separation of duties, enforced immutability, and full traceability from request to consumption. Compared to alternative approaches, it reduces supply-chain risk, prevents unauthorized artifacts from entering execution environments, and provides a scalable, repeatable governance framework aligned with enterprise security and compliance expectatio
